content:
I'm saving time during the week, definitely. It's great to know that I have a bunch of ingredients already cooked and ready to go, so I can just throw something together quickly. And it's not just about saving time, but also about reducing stress - I don't have to worry about what I'm going to make for lunch or dinner every day.

As for my overall health and energy levels, I do feel like I've noticed an improvement. I've been trying to eat more plant-based, and cooking at home has allowed me to control the ingredients and make healthier choices. Plus, I've been experimenting with new cooking techniques like sous vide and air frying, which have been a game-changer for healthier snacks and sides.
